*[[National Memorial Cemetery of Arizona#Notable monuments|World War II Submarine Torpedo monument]]
*[[National Navy UDT-SEAL Museum#UDT-SEAL Memorial|UDT-SEAL Memorial]]
*Various memorials for Lt. [[Vincent Robert Capodanno#Honors and awards|Vincent R. Capodanno]]<ref>Lt. Capodanno was a Navy chaplain who was posthumously awarded the Medal of Honor for his actions during the Vietnam War.</ref>
*[[Fairfield University Men's Rugby Football Club#Rugby Pitch|Lt. Hans Grauert Memorial Field]]<ref>'''Lt. Hans Grauert Memorial Field''' is the home [[rugby pitch]] of the Fairfield University Men's Rugby Football Club. Dr. Christopher Grauert (Class of 1968) and his mother, Leila B. Grauert, donated the rugby pitch in 2003 in honor of his brother, Lt. Hans Grauert, who was a [[naval aviator]] lost at sea during the [[Vietnam War]].</ref>
*[[Ensign C. Markland Kelly, Jr. Award]]<ref>The '''Ensign C. Markland Kelly, Jr. Award''' is a college lacrosse award. It is named for Charles Markland Kelly, Jr., a [[Maryland Terrapins men's lacrosse]] goalie who left school in 1940 to become a Navy pilot and died in the Battle of Midway. With [[World War II]] imminent, Kelly left school in October 1940, to become a Navy pilot. In August 1941, he received his wings and was commissioned an [[ensign]]. He was assigned to duty as a [[fighter pilot]] with Fighter [[Squadron (aviation)|]] 8 (VF-8) onboard [[USS Hornet (CV-8)|USS Hornet]]. Flying a [[Grumman F4F Wildcat]] on an [[escort fighter|escort]] mission for the carrier's [[bomber]]s during the [[Battle of Midway]], he failed to return from the initial [[Airstrike|strike]], and was reported [[missing in action]] on June 4, 1942.</ref>
*[[McLaughlin Award|Lt. Donald McLaughlin Jr. Award]]<ref>The '''Lt. Donald McLaughlin Jr. Award''' <U+2014> also known as the "Don McLaughlin Award" <U+2014> has been given annually since 1973 by the [[United States Intercollegiate Lacrosse Association]] (USILA) to the nation's most outstanding college lacrosse midfielder in [[NCAA]] [[Division I (NCAA)|Division I]], [[Division II (NCAA)|Division II]], and [[Division III (NCAA)|Division III]]. The award is named for Lt. (j.g.) Donald MacLaughlin Jr. (U.S. Naval Academy Class of 1963), an [[All-American]], [[Navy Midshipmen men's lacrosse|Navy lacrosse]] midfielder, who died on a combat mission in South Vietnam in 1966.</ref>
*John's Law<ref>'''John's Law''' is a [[New Jersey Legislature|New Jersey]] state [[statute]] that requires police to impound the vehicle of a driver who is being arrested for drunk driving. '''John's Law II''' is a subsequent New Jersey statute that authorizes police to hold drunken drivers until they sober up rather than release them to a relative or friend. The law is named for '''Ensign John R. Elliott''' (U.S. Naval Academy, Class of 2000), who was killed in 2000 by a drunken driver. The driver had been arrested two hours earlier, but he was released to the custody of a friend who allowed him to return to his vehicle and drive. Pearsall, Richard, [http://www.herocampaign.org/press_releases/Johns-Law-Courier.doc 'John's Law' may set the standard]. Courier-Post (Cherry Hill, N.J.), August 11, 2005. Retrieved 2010-02-15. See also [http://www.herocampaign.org/pdf/HERO-College-August09.ppt Ensign John R. Elliott HERO Campaign for Designated Drivers] website. Retrieved 2010-05-28.</ref>

